OL,3,C'History is repeating itself': Dozens
OL,4,Cof displaced islanders without home in
OL,5,CUK
OL,7,FOn Monday 10 June, around 52 people
OL,8,Farrived from Mauritius and are being
OL,9,Fhoused in a leisure centre in Crawley,
OL,10,Fwhile suitable accommodation is found.
OL,12,FCrawley in West Sussex has become home
OL,13,Fto the largest community in the UK,
OL,14,Fwith around 3,500 people and the
OL,15,Fgovernment are forecasting another
OL,16,F5,000 to take up the offer.
OL,18,FChagos Islander, Mary Eloyswe Douce
OL,19,Fsaid: "Life was very difficult, even
OL,20,Fwhen you study you can't find a job.
